{
  "page": "Spotted Tom",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Spotted Tom</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nSpotted Tom the Butcher</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Band_of_Nine\" title=\"Band of Nine\">Band of Nine</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westerosi</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Tom</b>, dubbed <b>Spotted Tom the Butcher</b>, was the captain of a <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellsword</a> company in the <a href=\"/index.php/Disputed_Lands\" title=\"Disputed Lands\">Disputed Lands</a> who became one of the infamous <a href=\"/index.php/Band_of_Nine\" title=\"Band of Nine\">Band of Nine</a>, the instigators of the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Ninepenny_Kings\" title=\"War of the Ninepenny Kings\">War of the Ninepenny Kings</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Spotted_Tom&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Band_of_Nine\" title=\"Band of Nine\">Band of Nine</a> were a group of merchants, sellswords and pirates who joined together to carve kingdoms out for themselves.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Spotted_Tom&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In an early draft of <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, it is said that Tom's unspecified company are the <a href=\"/index.php/Maiden%27s_Men\" title=\"Maiden&#39;s Men\">Maiden's Men</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Spotted_Tom&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Jaehaerys II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Reddit: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/asoiaf/comments/10cq27q/spoilers_extended_secrets_of_the_cushing_library/\">Secrets of the Cushing Library: The Grand Finale by u/gsteff</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404224022\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.112 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.944 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 496/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10430/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 3533/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 606/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1475/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.300/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.43 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  913.014      1 -total\n 98.73%  901.389      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 98.38%  898.239      1 Template:Infobox\n 10.81%   98.681     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  3.10%   28.288      4 Template:Infobox_label\n  0.93%    8.527      2 Template:Ref\n  0.62%    5.618      2 Template:Ref/core\n  0.27%    2.496      1 Template:References\n  0.11%    0.999      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:18801-0!canonical and timestamp 20260404224021 and revision id 311968\n -->\n",
